President Obama expressed his sadness over the passing of Jaime Escalante, known for his work teaching inner-city students calculus. While most people knew him through the movie based on his life, the true testament to his work was the students whose lives he changed. Escalante opened doors of success and higher education for his students, proving that their backgrounds did not determine their potential. He not only instilled knowledge but also helped them find passion and will to fulfill their potential. The President acknowledged Escalante as a representative of countless dedicated teachers across the country who positively impact the lives of young people. President Obama offered his condolences to Escalante's family and all those who knew him.